<P>To determine the value of the future advan|tage: &s;uppo&s;e even the annual increa&s;e of the expence of maintaining the poor in the old mode dimini&s;hed &frac13;, this can only be true in ca&s;e the price of provi&s;ions advance with no more than &frac23; the pre&s;ent celerity; con&s;equently the expence of maintaining the paupers in the hou&s;e will follow the &s;ame law,<NOTE N="&dagger;" PLACE="foot">Note D.</NOTE> the pre&s;ent
<PB N="14" REF="15">
value of all the future payments, had there been no act of incorporation, would be&mdash;&pound;. 105565
