<DIV2 N="3" TYPE="article">
<HEAD><HI>ARTICLE III.</HI> On the Increa&s;e of the Charge and Burthen, of Poors Rates. <HI>HYPOTHESIS.</HI></HEAD>
<P>WHEN the price of labour remains con|&s;tant, and the price of nece&s;&s;aries in|crea&s;e, the number of poor to be &s;upported by the public &s;hall increa&s;e at lea&s;t in the &s;ame pro|portion.</P>
<P>It is ea&s;y to demon&s;trate that this &s;uppo&s;ition falls &s;hort of the truth; the paupers who receive weekly collection in a very populous di&s;trict, being lately numbered amounted to 700; tho&s;e of one &s;ingle pari&s;h which pays &frac13; of the rates are in the whole far more than double that num|ber: let us &s;uppo&s;e that 1/6 of the number re|ceive collection; double the price of provi&s;ion
<PB N="88" REF="89">
without increa&s;ing that of labour, and &frac23; of the whole number of poor could infallibly become chargeable: but the hypothe&s;is gives the in|crea&s;ed number only 2/6 or &frac13;.</P>
