<P>Of the ab&s;olute burthen of the poors rate, let us &s;uppo&s;e its pre&s;ent amount 2,500,000, that &s;um is &frac14; of our taxes, the burthen of the taxes is 1s. 10&frac12;d. in the pound; that of the poor rate is nearly 5&frac34;d. If we compare it with the rents of the kingdom, it will appear to be 2s. 2&frac12;d. in the pound.</P>
<P>If we take the land tax as a &s;tandard to e&s;ti|mate it by, it exceeds it in proportion of 3 to 2; or is equal a land tax and a half at 4s. in the pound, or 2 of 3.</P>
